RIBCAGE

ribcage is the bony cage that protects the heart and lungs
it is not a passive shield: ribcage actively expands and contracts with each breath, working with the diaphragm to draw air into and out of the lungs
ribcage is also the anchor for many muscles of the upper body and the suspension framework for the heart through the pericardial fascia

